---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Cafe & Bar East London | Speciality Coffee & Light Bites | The Hackney, Hackney Road E2" description="Dog-friendly cafe-bar inside a restored 1860s brewery on Hackney Road, East London. Speciality coffee, craft cocktails, natural wines. Two minutes from Cambridge Heath station. Walk-ins welcome.">
<!-- ==================== NAVIGATION ==================== -->
  

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 1: HERO ==================== -->
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-bg" role="img" aria-label="The Hackney cafe-bar interior with exposed brick and natural light"></div>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <div class="eyebrow">Cafe & Bar - Hackney Road, East London E2</div>
        <h1>Speciality Coffee In A Restored 1860s Brewery.</h1>
        <p class="hero-sub">A dog-friendly cafe with high ceilings, skylights and hanging greenery — two minutes from Cambridge Heath station.</p>
        <a href="#menu" class="btn btn-primary">See The Menu</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 2: THE SPACE ==================== -->
  <section class="the-space fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="the-space-inner">
        <div class="the-space-text">
          <div class="section-label">The Space</div>
          <h2>A Proper Cafe-Bar In East London</h2>
          <p>We are at 503 Hackney Road, London E2 9ED, right between Bethnal Green and Cambridge Heath. The building is a former Victorian brewery with high ceilings, exposed brick, a skylit winter garden and a covered courtyard terrace.</p>
          <p>It is a nice place to sit with a laptop, meet someone for coffee, or come for drinks after work. Free wifi, plenty of plug sockets, and a good atmosphere all day.</p>
          <p>Dogs are welcome. You do not need to book. Just walk in.</p>
          <p class="history-note">Some of you might remember us as the Hackney Coffee Company. We started as a speciality coffee house, and good coffee is still at the heart of what we do. The space has grown since then, but the coffee has not changed.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="the-space-images">
          <div class="space-placeholder lazy-bg" data-bg="" data-bg-pos="center center" role="img" aria-label="The Hackney winter garden with natural light and greenery"></div>
          <div class="space-placeholder lazy-bg" data-bg="" data-bg-pos="center center" role="img" aria-label="The Hackney bar area with exposed brick"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 3: WHAT WE SERVE ==================== -->
  <section class="serve fade-in" id="menu">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="serve-header">
        <div class="section-label">The Menu</div>
        <h2>What We Serve</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="serve-grid">
        <div class="serve-category">
          <h3>Coffee & Drinks</h3>
          <p>Speciality coffee made properly. Espresso, flat whites, long blacks, oat milk as standard. We also do teas, fresh juices and soft drinks.</p>
          <p>We also serve natural wines by the glass, beers on tap and soft drinks. For cocktails and evening dining, check out our <a href="/supper-club/" style="color:var(--fired-brick);text-decoration:underline;">Supper Club</a> nights.</p>
          <p class="serve-highlight">We make a good Negroni.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="serve-category">
          <h3>Food</h3>
          <p>Light bites through the day. Pastries in the morning, seasonal snacks and bar food as the day goes on.</p>
          <p>Nothing complicated, just well-made food to go with your drink.</p>
          <p>Our in-house kitchen is led by Chef Marco Mannoni. Seasonal menus, locally sourced ingredients, modern European cooking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline-dark">Download Full Menu (PDF)</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 4: OPENING HOURS ==================== -->
  <section class="hours fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="hours-inner">
        <div class="section-label" style="color:var(--dusty-coral);">Opening Hours</div>
        <h2>Opening Hours</h2>

        <div class="hours-table">
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Monday</span><span>Closed</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Tuesday</span><span>8 am – 4 pm</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Wednesday</span><span>8 am – 5 pm</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Thursday</span><span>8 am – 5 pm</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Friday</span><span>8 am – 5 pm</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Saturday</span><span>9 am – 5 pm</span></div>
          <div class="hours-row"><span>Sunday</span><span>9 am – 4 pm</span></div>
        </div>

        <div class="hours-note">
          <p>On days when the venue is booked for a private event, the cafe-bar may close earlier than usual. Check Google Maps for today's live hours before heading over.</p>
        </div>

        <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/RwT31Y6tmXPzyqGQ9" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-outline">Check Today's Hours on Google</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 5: FIND US ==================== -->
  <section class="find-us fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="find-us-inner">
        <div class="find-us-details">
          <div class="section-label">Location</div>
          <h2>Find Us</h2>
          <div class="find-us-address">503 Hackney Road<br>London, E2 9ED</div>

          <ul class="transport-list">
            <li>Cambridge Heath Overground - 2 minute walk</li>
            <li>Bethnal Green Underground (Central line) - 8 minute walk</li>
            <li>Bus routes 106, 254 and D6 stop directly outside</li>
          </ul>

          <p class="parking-note">No customer parking on site, but Hackney Road has free parking from 7pm onwards.</p>

          <a href="https://maps.app.goo.gl/RwT31Y6tmXPzyqGQ9" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn btn-primary">Get Directions</a>
        </div>
        <div class="find-us-map">
          <span class="map-placeholder-text">Map - coming soon</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 6: FAQs ==================== -->
  <section class="faqs fade-in">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="faqs-header">
        <div class="section-label">FAQs</div>
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Is The Hackney cafe-bar dog friendly?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. Dogs are welcome inside and on the terrace.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Do I need to book a table?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">No. The cafe-bar is walk-in only. Just turn up.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>What are the opening hours?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">We're open Tuesday to Sunday (closed Mondays). Weekdays from 8am, weekends from 9am. Hours may change when the venue hosts a private event, so check Google Maps for today's live hours.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Is this the same place as Hackney Coffee Company?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. We started as the Hackney Coffee Company and rebranded to The Hackney. Same building, same coffee, same team.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Can I work from the cafe?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">Yes. We have free wifi, plug sockets, and plenty of space during the day. Lots of freelancers and remote workers use us as a regular spot.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <button class="faq-question">
            <span>Where exactly is The Hackney cafe-bar?</span>
            <span class="faq-icon">+</span>
          </button>
          <div class="faq-answer">
            <div class="faq-answer-inner">503 Hackney Road, London E2 9ED. Two minutes walk from Cambridge Heath Overground, eight minutes from Bethnal Green Underground on the Central line.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== SECTION 7: CROSS-SELL ==================== -->
  <section class="cross-sell">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-label">More Than A Cafe</div>
      <h2>Planning Something Special?</h2>
      <p class="cross-sell-body">From intimate weddings to private parties, The Hackney hosts it all. Same building, same team, same attention to detail.</p>
      <div class="cross-sell-buttons">
        <a href="/weddings/" class="btn btn-primary">Explore Weddings</a>
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-outline">Explore Events</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== FOOTER ==================== -->
  

  <!-- ==================== JAVASCRIPT ==================== -->
</Base>
